text.__SUMMARY__: Shorea negrosensis (called, along with some other species in the genus Shorea, red lauan) is a species of plant in the Dipterocarpaceae family. It is endemic to the Philippines.
text.Sources: Ashton, P. (1998). "Shorea negrosensis". The IUCN Red List of Threatened Species. IUCN. 1998: e.T33144A9762403. doi:10.2305/IUCN.UK.1998.RLTS.T33144A9762403.en.
